page.title: 20AUTHORS' ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS
page.content:
These pages about Freeland and Church Hanborough were written by the upper juniors at Eynsham Primary School. There are about 90 children aged 9 to 11 in the upper juniors and during the months of June and July we went in small groups in the minibus to look at different things.
We would like to thank the upper juniors at Freeland Primary School, Miss Breakspear of St.Mary's Church, Miss Gibson at Church Hanborough, Mr.Symington of Cook's Corner Farm, Mr.Webster of Webster's Nurseries and Mr.Warburton, the manager of Isis Fish Farm. Mr. and Mrs.Davidson of Freeland, and Mr.Jackson, head of Freeland Primary School also gave us a lot of help.
